summary: We are 22 days away from the March 8th release of Captain Marvel (::EXCITED SCREECHES::), and the publicity campaign is in full...
body:
We are 22 days away from the March 8th release of Captain Marvel (::EXCITED SCREECHES::), and the publicity campaign is in full swing. Today cast members Brie Larson (Carol Danvers, Captain Marvel herself), Samuel L. Jackson (Nick Fury), Gemma Chan (Minn-Nerva), and directors Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck started off the tour with an appearance at a fan event in Singapore.

Sigh, the asian countries get the coolest events. Good for them!

Check out the photos below:

This slideshow requires JavaScript.

From Disney:

Set in the 1990s, Marvel Studios’ “Captain Marvel” is an all-new adventure from a previously unseen period in the history of the Marvel Cinematic Universe that follows the journey of Carol Danvers as she becomes one of the universe’s most powerful heroes. While a galactic war between two alien races reaches Earth, Danvers finds herself and a small cadre of allies at the center of the maelstrom. 

The film stars Brie Larson, Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Rune Temte, Algenis Perez Soto, Mckenna Grace, with Annette Bening, with Clark Gregg, and Jude Law.

Marvel Studios’ “Captain Marvel” is produced by Kevin Feige and directed by Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck. Louis D’Esposito, Victoria Alonso, Jonathan Schwartz, Patricia Whitcher and Stan Lee are the executive producers. The story is by Nicole Perlman & Meg LeFauve and Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck & Geneva Robertson-Dworet, and the screenplay is by Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck & Geneva Robertson-Dworet.

Follow the social media pages:

Website and Mobile site:  www.marvel.com/captainmarvel

Like us on Facebook: www.facebook.com/marvelstudios

Follow us on Twitter:   www.twitter.com/marvelstudios

Instagram: www.Instagram.com/marvelstudios

Captain Marvel hits theatres March 8th. Tickets are on sale now.

Captain Marvel: Cast Members descend on Singapore for Fan Event (Photos) We are 22 days away from the March 8th release of Captain Marvel (::EXCITED SCREECHES::), and the publicity campaign is in full swing.

summary: March 8th is fast approaching, and that means the first female driven entry into the Marvel Cinematic Unvierse, Captain Marvel...
body:
March 8th is fast approaching, and that means the first female driven entry into the Marvel Cinematic Unvierse, Captain Marvel is about to hit our screens. The closer we get to release, the more promotional material we’re bound to receive, and today that means an introduction into the characters of Captain Marvel with promotional posters for each one.

Check them out in the gallery below:

This slideshow requires JavaScript.

Set in the 1990s, Marvel Studios’ “Captain Marvel” is an all-new adventure from a previously unseen period in the history of the Marvel Cinematic Universe that follows the journey of Carol Danvers as she becomes one of the universe’s most powerful heroes. While a galactic war between two alien races reaches Earth, Danvers finds herself and a small cadre of allies at the center of the maelstrom. 

The film stars Brie Larson, Samuel L. Jackson, Ben Mendelsohn, Djimon Hounsou, Lee Pace, Lashana Lynch, Gemma Chan, Rune Temte, Algenis Perez Soto, Mckenna Grace, with Annette Bening, with Clark Gregg, and Jude Law.

Marvel Studios’ “Captain Marvel” is produced by Kevin Feige and directed by Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck. Louis D’Esposito, Victoria Alonso, Jonathan Schwartz, Patricia Whitcher and Stan Lee are the executive producers. The story is by Nicole Perlman & Meg LeFauve and Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck & Geneva Robertson-Dworet, and the screenplay is by Anna Boden & Ryan Fleck & Geneva Robertson-Dworet.

Captain Marvel hits theatres on March 8th, International Womens Day, and tickets are already on sale. So if you haven’t purchased yours yet, what are you waiting for?

And make sure you follow all the social media pages for Captain Marvel:

Website and Mobile site:  www.marvel.com/captainmarvel

Like us on Facebook: www.facebook.com/marvelstudios

Follow us on Twitter:   www.twitter.com/marvelstudios

Instagram: www.Instagram.com/marvelstudios
